{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἐρευν-άω</b>, <br /> also <b>ἐρευν-ίω</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “GDI” 5075.35 (from Crete)\">Refs</a>], and <b>ἐραυνάω</b> (which see):— <b>seek</b> or <b>search for, search after, track,</b> ἴχνι᾽ ἐρευνῶντες κύνες ἤϊσαν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 19.436; μετ᾽ ἀνέρος ἴχνι᾽ ἐρευνῶν 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 18.321; τεύχε᾽ ἐ. 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 22.180; τὴν σοφὴν εὐβουλίαν 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 1038; θεῶν βουλεύματ᾽ 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “Fragmenta.” 61; νεκρούς 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Medea” 1318; κακούργους 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 1.2.12; ἄν τινα οἴωμαι σοφὸν εἶναι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Apologia” 23b. compare 41b; τὸ γραμματεῖον 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 25.61 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ὧν..ἂν θεὸς χρείαν ἐρευνᾷ the things whereof he <b>seeks after</b> the use, i.e. whatever things he finds serviceable, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 725. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>search, explore</b> a place, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 5.92.δ᾽, 2nd c.AD: Soranus Medicus “Vit.Hippocr.” 3 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τεναγέων ῥοάς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 3.24; ὄρος 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 25.221; τοὺς ὑπόπτους τῶν τόπων 2nd-3rd c.AD: Aelianus “Tactica - Griechische Kriegsschriftsteller” 17: _absolutely_, εὑρήσεις ἐρευνῶν\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] thou wilt find <b>by searching,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 13.113, compare 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 268; εἰσβάντες εἰς τὸ πλοῖον ἠρεύνων 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 5.29. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>inquire after,</b> φάτιν [<a hre